  "body": "Does `@truffle/contract` do any sort of verification amid instantiating JSON contract artifacts? I mistakenly imported another variables into constructor and it didn't crash. However it did throw an expected exception on `deployed()` method because naturally the artifact was invalid and contract was not deployed, however I can't know that. \r\n\r\nHave the following code:\r\n```js\r\nimport truffleContract from \"@truffle/contract\";\r\n\r\n(async function(){\r\n\r\n  const res = await get(\"/contracts\");\r\n\r\n  /**\r\n  * @type { Array<Json Contract Artifact Object> }\r\n  */\r\n  const contractsObj = res.data;\r\n\r\n  /**\r\n  * @type { {string: Truffle Contract} }\r\n  */\r\n  const contracts = {};\r\n  \r\n  for (const contractObj of contractsObj) {\r\n    const contractTruffle = truffleContract(contractsObj); // mistake here\r\n  \r\n    contractTruffle.setProvider(window.ethereum);\r\n  \r\n    contracts[contractObj.contractName] = contractTruffle;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  await contracts.SomeContract.deployed(); // throws famous exception here\r\n})();\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere is a mistake, on line 18: instead of using _contractObj_, `truffleContract()` uses _contract**s**Obj_ as parameter. Even thought the artifact is invalid it doesn't throw an error. Execution carries on until line 25, in which the famous one is thrown:\r\n> Uncaught (in promise) Error: Contract has not been deployed to detected network (network/artifact mismatch)\r\n\r\nThe exception message itself **is valid**, because **I have imported invalid artifacts** and it's not deployed on network, however **I don't know** I imported invalid artifacts because I got **no exception** on line 18. Furthermore if you `console.log(contracts.SomeContract)` it will appear as a normal truffle contract object, which would give no clue for newbies related to debugging. \r\n\r\nI believe we should add artifact checker amid contract instantiation. Is there a reason it shouldn't be?",
